Privacy Policy for Meta-analysis & Systematic Review API
Effective Date: [2025]
Version: 1.0

This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and protect your data when you use the Meta-analysis & Systematic Review API ("the Service"). By using the Service, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.

1. Information We Collect
We collect information that is necessary to provide the Service. This may include:

Personal Information: If you provide any personal information, such as your name, email address, or contact information while creating an account or interacting with the API, we will store that information securely.

API Usage Data: We collect information about how you use the API, such as the types of requests made, timestamps, and metadata related to those requests.

Content Data: Any text, research questions, systematic review texts, meta-analysis texts, or other data that you submit through the API. This data is used solely for the purpose of processing and enhancing your content.

2. How We Use Your Information
The information we collect is used for the following purposes:

To provide and maintain the API service.

To improve the Service by analyzing usage patterns and errors.

To personalize your experience and optimize search queries, data extractions, and enhancements.

To communicate with you about your API requests, issues, and updates related to the Service.

To comply with legal obligations and enforce our Terms of Service.

3. Data Security
We take the security of your data seriously. We implement a variety of security measures, including:

Encryption: Data transmitted via the API is encrypted to protect against unauthorized access.

Access Controls: Only authorized personnel have access to the stored data. We use secure authentication methods (API keys, OAuth) to ensure that only you can access your data.

Regular Audits: We conduct regular audits of our security systems to ensure that your data remains protected.

4. Sharing Your Information
We do not share your data with third parties except in the following circumstances:

Service Providers: We may share your data with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in operating the Service. These service providers are bound by confidentiality agreements and are prohibited from using your data for any other purpose.

Legal Compliance: If required by law, we may disclose your data to government authorities or other parties as necessary to comply with legal obligations.

5. Your Rights
You have the following rights regarding your data:

Access: You may request access to the data we have collected about you.

Correction: You can update or correct your personal information or API data through your account settings or by contacting us.

Deletion: You may request the deletion of your personal information or any data submitted through the API.

Data Portability: You may request a copy of your data in a machine-readable format.

To exercise these rights, please contact us at [contact email].

6. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we make changes, we will post the updated policy on this page and update the "Effective Date" at the top of the policy. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically to stay informed about how we are protecting your data.

7. Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or how we handle your data, please contact us at:

